[ Thu Oct 20 23:08:10 2016 ]
Sadly Mom's car wouldn't start, and the key got stuck in the ignition again.  Did a bit of research and found that you could open up a port under the stearing wheel and push a button that supposedly moves a solenoid that allows the key to come out.  Annoying...but at least we found a solution to that.  Unfortunately it appeared that the battery was dead also.  

Anyways...had to find the battery which ended up being in the trunk...it's charging now.

On a side note, I found a bottle of Metformin on one of my walks...of course I then found out that this stuff is magic for people doing ketosis diets.  It kicks you into ketosis much faster, and allows you to glucose load your muscles during your cheat days.  Looking forward to exploring what it can do.


