[ Wed Nov  2 21:14:45 2016 ]
Today is the second day of NaNoWriMo.  I haven't written anything this month.  Sadly, I'm a little stuck as to how to proceed.  I don't really like the story that I'm in as of now, and I don't know where to take it.  I realize that it's only a first draft and by the time that I'm done there will be a lot on the floor, but it's definitely hard to proceed.  Lot's of it is trying to organize all that I've done and all that I want to do.  I also don't have a comfortable place to write.  There is always noise and distraction at home with Ayrin's kids around.  Excuses really.  I could put in headphones, I could switch to a different chair, or go out to the carriage house.  

I'm also at a loss of how I want to write.  I've been writing by hand, which is good for distractions, but not good for editing.  I am not looking forward to writing out everything that I've already writen by hand again.  And since it will take awhile to do that, I'm stuck as to how to proceed with new work.  Do I continue on by hand, or do I write in an editor and then go back and fill in the blanks later.  It all adds up to more distractions.

Not to mention that this laptop dies immediately.  I've been trying to use the tablet, but the keyboard interaction is just not quite there.

Been trying to build a raspberry pi emacs computer, but all of the displays are more expensive than a monitor, or worse than the tablet's capabilities. Hopefully between the new battery that I just ordered and the battery bank that I put together, I'll have a semi mobile laptop once again.  We'll see.


