[ Fri Feb 17 10:42:22 2017 ]
Algorithms are technology.  The ability to do something is a technological advantage.
Furthermore, the ability to do something efficiently is a further technological advantage. By making algorithms available one can provide the building blocks to recreate that technology.  When the building blocks step back to the raw materials provided by nature one can essential recreate the technology from scratch.

Each algorithm has an input and an output.  They are recipes, each containing a list of ingredients and tools to create a product.  These products can further be ingredients for more complicated recipes, just as the ingredients for one particular recipe is often a preprocessed outcome of a previously manufactured process.  By stepping back through the processes one can reach a point where all of the ingredients are available with ones current available resources.  This is self sufficency.  This is made from scratch.

